%N A394805 Decimal expansion of 6 * arcsin(1/3) / Pi.
%C A394805 The probability that four points selected independently and distributed according to the same normal distribution in the plane form the vertices of a convex quadrilateral (Maehara, 1978; Blatter, 2008).
%C A394805 The probability that in a sample of 4 independent variables distributed according to the same normal distribution the mean lies between 2nd and 3rd variable when they are arranged in increasing order of magnitude (David, 1963). The probability that it lies between 1st and 2nd and the probability that it lies between 3rd and 4th are both 3*arccos(1/3)/Pi - 1 = 0.175479656... .
%C A394805 The probability that the intersection of a cube with random plane that passes through its center is a quadrilateral (see A349605).
%C A394805 The probability that the projection of a regular tetrahedron at a random direction is a quadrilateral (Affentranger and Schneider, 1992; Finch, 2012).
%C A394805 The probability that the projection of a regular octahedron at a random direction is a quadrilateral (Böröczky and Henk, 1999; Finch, 2012).
%D A394805 Hiroshi Maehara, On Sylvester's problem, Proc. Inst. Stat. Math., Tokyo, Vol. 25 (1978), pp. 81-86.
%H A394805 Fernando Affentranger and Rolf Schneider, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02187839">Random projections of regular simplices</a>, Discrete & Computational Geometry, Vol. 7, No. 3 (1992), pp. 219-226.
%H A394805 Christian Blatter, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/27642611">Four Shots for a Convex Quadrilateral</a>, The American Mathematical Monthly, Vol. 115, No. 9 (2008), pp. 837-843.
%H A394805 Károly Böröczky, Jr. and Martin Henk, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s000130050424">Random projections of regular polytopes</a>, Archiv der Mathematik, Vol. 73, No. 6 (1999), pp. 465-473; <a href="https://opus4.kobv.de/opus4-zib/frontdoor/index/index/docId/290">preprint</a>.
%H A394805 Swee Hong Chan, Gil Kalai, Bhargav Narayanan, Natalya Ter-Saakov, and Moshe White, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2507.01353">Unimodality for Radon partitions of random vectors, arXiv:2507.01353 [math.CO], 2025.
%H A394805 Herbert T. David, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/2991281">The sample mean among the extreme normal order statistics</a>, The Annals of Mathematical Statistics, Vol. 34, No. 1 (1963), pp. 33-55.
%H A394805 Steven R. Finch, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1203.2464">Planar Projections and Second Intrinsic Volume</a>, arXiv:1203.2464 [math.MG], 2012.
%H A394805 Florian Frick, Andrew Newman, and Wesley Pegden, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1112/mtk.70015">Youden's demon is Sylvester's problem</a>, Mathematika, Vol. 71, No. 2 (2025), Article e70015; <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2407.02589">arXiv preprint</a>, arXiv:2407.02589 [math.PR], 2024.
%H A394805 Hugo Panzo, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.spl.2024.110349">Sylvester's problem for random walks and bridges</a>, Statistics & Probability Letters, Vol. 219 (2025), Article 110349; <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2409.07927">arXiv preprint</a>, arXiv:2409.07927 [math.PR], 2024.
%H A394805 Eric Weisstein's MathWorld, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/SylvestersFour-PointProblem.html">Sylvester's Four-Point Problem</a>.
